**Emergency Steps:**  
- Locate and turn off the water shut-off valve to stop the water flow into the house.  
- Identify visible leaks and place a container underneath to collect water, preventing damage.  
- Use bottled water or boil tap water for at least one minute before drinking to ensure safety.  
- Avoid using appliances that require water until the issue is resolved.  
- Contact San Jose Water for further assistance and guidance on the situation.

**Non-Emergency Tips:**  
- For billing inquiries or to make payments, visit the [billing and payments section](https://www.sjwater.com/payments) on their website.  
- Stay informed about service alerts and updates by checking the customer care section on their website.  
- To start or stop water service, you can submit a request online or contact their customer service via phone or email [sjwater.com](https://www.sjwater.com/myservice).